                    <span>If you have never done any C/C++ for WIN32, don't expect to know just what the heck Mr Pazera is talking about. Although, if you haven't any other books in your library related to _C/C++_Game_programming_, and are die-hard to learn ISO-HEX; start here - and STUDY LIKE CRAZY! By this I mean memorize the first few chapters. It is detrimental to the rest of the book. Although it's still best to start with some knowlege of C/C++; it's not imperative in this book if you are diligent. Have fun, enjoy, and Good Luck!:></span>
                  
              
